History




Karl Dietrich Bracher obituary









Political scientist who examined the collapse of the Weimar Republic in 1930s Germany and the rise of Hitler and nazism






















































Karl Dietrich Bracher’s The Dissolution of the Weimar Republic was the first serious attempt to explain the collapse of Germany’s first democracy.
Photograph: Weychardt/Ullstein Bild/Getty










History




Karl Dietrich Bracher obituary









Political scientist who examined the collapse of the Weimar Republic in 1930s Germany and the rise of Hitler and nazism












Share on Facebook









Share on Twitter









Share via Email
















View more sharing options




Share on LinkedIn









